---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Container from "../components/Container.astro";
import PageIntro from "../components/PageIntro.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Starter privacy policy for a small 3D print-on-demand service website."
  pathname="/privacy-policy/"
>
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    description="Starter policy for a small 3D print-on-demand business. This page should be reviewed and customized with the final business entity, contact details, jurisdiction, and any platform-specific requirements before launch."
  />

  <section class="section-shell">
    <Container>
      <article class="legal-copy max-w-4xl">
        <section>
          <p>Effective date: April 28, 2026</p>
          <p>
            This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>[Insert legal business name]</strong> collects,
            uses, stores, and shares personal information when you visit this website, request a
            quote, upload files, or contact the business about 3D printing services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Information Collected</h2>
          <p>The business may collect the following information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Name, email address, and company name if provided</li>
            <li>Project notes, print requirements, and requested deadlines</li>
            <li>Uploaded design files, models, drawings, photos, or measurements</li>
            <li>Messages sent through quote or contact forms</li>
            <li>Basic technical information such as browser type, device type, and site usage data if analytics tools are enabled</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
          <p>Information may be used to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Respond to quote requests and customer inquiries</li>
            <li>Review uploaded models and determine whether a print job is feasible</li>
            <li>Recommend materials, finishes, timelines, and fulfillment options</li>
            <li>Communicate about production, delivery, pickup, invoicing, or revisions</li>
            <li>Improve the website and customer experience</li>
            <li>Maintain records for business operations, legal compliance, and dispute resolution</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Design Files And Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>
            Customer-uploaded design files and related project information may contain sensitive or
            proprietary information. The business should describe here what level of confidentiality
            it is willing to provide, how files are stored, who can access them, and whether
            separate non-disclosure agreements are available.
          </p>
          <p>
            Placeholder for legal review: <strong>[Insert final confidentiality language and file retention policy]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Sharing Of Information</h2>
          <p>Personal information is not sold. Information may be shared only as needed with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Payment processors used to complete a transaction</li>
            <li>Shipping carriers used to deliver finished orders</li>
            <li>Hosting, form, analytics, or email service providers used to operate the website</li>
            <li>Professional advisers or authorities when legally required</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            Personal information and project files may be retained for as long as reasonably needed
            to respond to inquiries, complete orders, maintain business records, resolve disputes, or
            comply with legal obligations.
          </p>
          <p>
            Placeholder for legal review: <strong>[Insert final retention timelines for quote requests, project files, and customer communications]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Cookies And Analytics</h2>
          <p>
            If analytics, advertising pixels, or cookie-based tools are added to the website, this
            section should be updated to explain what tools are in use, what data they collect, and
            how users can opt out where required by law.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            Depending on where customers are located, they may have rights to request access to,
            correction of, or deletion of their personal information. They may also have rights to
            object to certain processing or withdraw consent where consent applies.
          </p>
          <p>
            Requests can be directed to: <strong>[Insert privacy contact email]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Security</h2>
          <p>
            Reasonable safeguards should be used to protect personal information and uploaded files.
            However, no online transmission or storage method is guaranteed to be completely secure.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            This website is not intended for children under the age of 13, and the business does not
            knowingly collect personal information directly from children.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Changes To This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. The current version should always
            be posted on this page with a revised effective date.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For privacy questions or requests, contact:
            <strong> [Insert legal business name, business address, and privacy contact email]</strong>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
